{"type":"message","id":"7f05ca54","parentId":"e579f94a","timestamp":"2026-03-10T04:20:10.328Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01AsKN4iyJ4gyc9N72jQ957b","toolName":"memory_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/19006541.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 8,\n      \"endLine\": 11,\n      \"score\": 0.87,\n      \"snippet\": \"@@ -8,4 @@ (7 before, 52 after)\\n\\nLooks like a great service. Our wedding is in Mexico City. Given most major US carriers (ATT/Verizon) include service in Mexico & Canada as part of the plan, I'd imagine guests won't have issues receiving txts during the week of the wedding?\\n\\nHave you had any experiences with Mexico yet? Thanks\\n\\nSource: memory/19006541.md#L8-L11\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/19006541.md#L8-L11\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/19006626.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 60,\n      \"endLine\": 63,\n      \"score\": 0.86,\n      \"snippet\": \"@@ -60,4 @@ (59 before, 30 after)\\n\\nBut... with that being said, we do have a lot of international weddings using WedTexts (including Mexico).\\n\\nThey do so because most international cell phone plans are able to receive the texts and anyone with a smartphone who is connected to wifi can also receive the messages.\\n\\nSource: memory/19006626.md#L60-L63\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/19006626.md#L60-L63\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"memory/19006594.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 8,\n      \"endLine\": 11,\n      \"score\": 0.81,\n      \"snippet\": \"@@ -8,4 @@ (7 before, 170 after)\\n\\nHello can I get a refund because my wedding is in mexico and Wedtexts isnt guaranteed to work there?\\n\\nOn Jun 29, 2024, at 6:01 AM, WedTexts <xxxxx@xxxxx.xxx> wrote:\\n\\nSource: memory/19006594.md#L8-L11\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/19006594.md#L8-L11\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"provider\": \"qmd\",\n  \"model\": \"qmd\",\n  \"citations\": \"auto\"\n}"}],"details":{"results":[{"path":"memory/19006541.md","startLine":8,"endLine":11,"score":0.87,"snippet":"@@ -8,4 @@ (7 before, 52 after)\n\nLooks like a great service. Our wedding is in Mexico City. Given most major US carriers (ATT/Verizon) include service in Mexico & Canada as part of the plan, I'd imagine guests won't have issues receiving txts during the week of the wedding?\n\nHave you had any experiences with Mexico yet? Thanks\n\nSource: memory/19006541.md#L8-L11","source":"memory","citation":"memory/19006541.md#L8-L11"},{"path":"memory/19006626.md","startLine":60,"endLine":63,"score":0.86,"snippet":"@@ -60,4 @@ (59 before, 30 after)\n\nBut... with that being said, we do have a lot of international weddings using WedTexts (including Mexico).\n\nThey do so because most international cell phone plans are able to receive the texts and anyone with a smartphone who is connected to wifi can also receive the messages.\n\nSource: memory/19006626.md#L60-L63","source":"memory","citation":"memory/19006626.md#L60-L63"},{"path":"memory/19006594.md","startLine":8,"endLine":11,"score":0.81,"snippet":"@@ -8,4 @@ (7 before, 170 after)\n\nHello can I get a refund because my wedding is in mexico and Wedtexts isnt guaranteed to work there?\n\nOn Jun 29, 2024, at 6:01 AM, WedTexts <xxxxx@xxxxx.xxx> wrote:\n\nSource: memory/19006594.md#L8-L11","source":"memory","citation":"memory/19006594.md#L8-L11"}],"provider":"qmd","model":"qmd","citations":"auto"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773116410325}}
{"type":"message","id":"7827c1b1","parentId":"7f05ca54","timestamp":"2026-03-10T04:20:13.841Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01ACkkxqHyJv4a9EeTmBjGGr","name":"memory_get","arguments":{"path":"memory/19006626.md","from":55,"lines":40}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01WeQybDLm3m2Yn4haAhNtZH","name":"memory_get","arguments":{"path":"memory/19006594.md","from":1,"lines":50}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":169,"cacheRead":12936,"cacheWrite":714,"totalTokens":13820,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.0042250000000000005,"cacheRead":0.006468,"cacheWrite":0.0044625,"total":0.0151605}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773116410327}}
{"type":"message","id":"b6e84215","parentId":"7827c1b1","timestamp":"2026-03-10T04:20:13.853Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01ACkkxqHyJv4a9EeTmBjGGr","toolName":"memory_get","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"text\": \"Thank you for your note and congrats on your upcoming wedding!\\n\\nRe: Wedding in Mexico & WiFi\\n\\nWedTexts is only guaranteed to work in the US with US cell phone numbers.\\n\\nBut... with that being said, we do have a lot of international weddings using WedTexts (including Mexico).\\n\\nThey do so because most international cell phone plans are able to receive the texts and anyone with a smartphone who is connected to wifi can also receive the messages.\\n\\n\\nRe: Email instead\\n\\nUnfortunately, no, sending them an email instead is not an option.\\n\\n\\nRe: # of texts sent\\n\\nFirst, every WedTexts account has UNLIMITED messages 🙃\\n\\nSecond, depending on the length of each WedTexts message, it will be received by your guests as one or multiple text messages.\\n\\nMost people's cell phone carriers and phones will receive those multiple SMS messages and display them as one.\\n\\n\\nI'd love for you to use WedTexts for your wedding if what I've said above might work for you.\\n\\nAlso, if you want to try WedTexts in Mexico, I'm happy to refund you after your wedding if it doesn't work for some reason.\\n\\nPlease let me know your decision.\\n\\nCheers,\\n\\nJames\\nCEO, WedTexts\\n\\n---\\n\",\n  \"path\": \"memory/19006626.md\"\n}"}],"details":{"text":"Thank you for your note and congrats on your upcoming wedding!\n\nRe: Wedding in Mexico & WiFi\n\nWedTexts is only guaranteed to work in the US with US cell phone numbers.\n\nBut... with that being said, we do have a lot of international weddings using WedTexts (including Mexico).\n\nThey do so because most international cell phone plans are able to receive the texts and anyone with a smartphone who is connected to wifi can also receive the messages.\n\n\nRe: Email instead\n\nUnfortunately, no, sending them an email instead is not an option.\n\n\nRe: # of texts sent\n\nFirst, every WedTexts account has UNLIMITED messages 🙃\n\nSecond, depending on the length of each WedTexts message, it will be received by your guests as one or multiple text messages.\n\nMost people's cell phone carriers and phones will receive those multiple SMS messages and display them as one.\n\n\nI'd love for you to use WedTexts for your wedding if what I've said above might work for you.\n\nAlso, if you want to try WedTexts in Mexico, I'm happy to refund you after your wedding if it doesn't work for some reason.\n\nPlease let me know your decision.\n\nCheers,\n\nJames\nCEO, WedTexts\n\n---\n","path":"memory/19006626.md"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773116413851}}
{"type":"message","id":"f4072970","parentId":"b6e84215","timestamp":"2026-03-10T04:20:13.863Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01WeQybDLm3m2Yn4haAhNtZH","toolName":"memory_get","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"text\": \"# Ticket #19006594\\n\\n**Subject:** Re: Built to answer your burning questions\\n\\n**Created:** 2024-06-29T20:50:13Z\\n\\n## Description\\n\\nHello can I get a refund because my wedding is in mexico and Wedtexts isnt guaranteed to work there?\\n\\nOn Jun 29, 2024, at 6:01 AM, WedTexts <xxxxx@xxxxx.xxx> wrote:\\n\\n﻿\\nHey Alliah, How crazy was yesterday’s wedding horror story?! If you want to read more stories like that one and posts by real\\n\\nHey Alliah,\\n\\nHow crazy was yesterday’s wedding horror story?!\\n\\nIf you want to read more stories like that one and posts by real wedding couples who’ve used WedTexts, you can find more here on our blog. (https://be324.keap-link017.com/v2/click/a9be9a0a7b9f752a0cb73e6bf7da5d94/eJyNUV1rwjAU_S-B-WRt6wdioYwiTorOh7E9S5pcali-SG7divjfl-j0ycHewjnnnnPPzYkgaKqx5qQgDUzGUzIkDpiwAjQujUbKLmSezbNZPiRS6M-1M50lxenR7J2P6CxfLIYEewtB8f5WLTf1br3f1rtNUFrqQsR_bCbzcTae3I1Wr1W9Jefzn86gBK6OwdyTAl0HsREXoRV-OBn0B0TrizRtpGlHX8ARvtGPmFEpowitcX3qgMrkRsUHF7r16XOHau9N5xiUEihPpPCYMKosFa0eRFaFqE6VoKiQF-DGlkJzw_bHLL_C4bZhxbIxvE9izGAVR0oqpaAH6Dw0wjxNszaicbnBi3Aed1RBWV00oSm1FjT__aYN9Ne-5x_m8qGM)\\n\\nSpeaking of our blog!\\n\\nOur blog is built to answer your questions, like:\\n\\nHow do I create my wedding budget? (https://be324.keap-link017.com/v2/click/87c10d1e32d75c46e358d3405ded0d16/eJyNUV1rwjAU_S-B-WRsrYpQKEPESdH5MLZnSZNLDcsX6Y2uiP99iW4-Odjr-brnJGeCYJjBWpCSNDAppmRIPHDpJBhcWoOMX8lxPs9n4yFR0nyuvQ2OlOdH3juf0FmRRwv2DqLi_W2x3NS79X5b7zZR6ZiPJ_4TM5kXeTG5B61eF_WWXC5_JoOWuDrG8I6U6AOkRULGVfjhVdQfEF1XZlmjbDs6gUD4wm7Erc4O9kTRUu6BIdDeBk8jL6RpaRNEC5g9B9T7LhIcKgVMUCU7pJxpx2RrBonV8VjQFWgm1RX4ZStphOX7Yz6-wfF1Y8mqsaKnqcNglSwVU0qyA4QOGmmfpnmb0FRv8CJ9hzumoVpcNXErcw6M-PmoDfS3xZdvyHih1g==)\\n\\nHow can I make my wedding guest